WEBVTT

00:00:00.151 --> 00:00:04.213
To be effective, four facets of CQ must be developed.

00:00:04.693 --> 00:00:12.496
First, let us examine metacognitive CQ, which is the mental capability to acquire and understand cultural knowledge,

00:00:13.056 --> 00:00:16.417
verifying assumptions during cross-cultural interactions.

00:00:17.138 --> 00:00:22.960
Moving on to the next block, cognitive CQ is the general knowledge about different cultures,

00:00:23.360 --> 00:00:25.221
norms, and business practices.

00:00:26.358 --> 00:00:34.463
Next, we have motivational CQ, which is the interest, confidence, and persistence in adapting to new cultural environments,

00:00:34.964 --> 00:00:36.565
even when friction occurs.

00:00:37.785 --> 00:00:44.770
Finally, behavioral CQ is the capability to exhibit appropriate verbal and nonverbal actions.
